This subsection is an addition to the AST_gridstations repo. This supports the ability to access data in a more parallel manner. Eg, 
running indeopendantly jobs based on products and stations lists. This is intended for execution by Pegasus. The launcher approach is to 
git clone this AST_gridstations data set and then let pegasus stage specific yaml data at required.

1) SOURCES
The current SOURCES supported by the AST underying code are:
NOAA_STATIONS, NDBC_BUOYS, NDBC_HISTORIC, USGS, USGS_RIVERS, CONTRAILS_COASTAL, CONTRAILS_RIVERS
 
The NDBC_HISTORIC data is a special case. NDBC only provides realtime data for the last 45 days. However, that does not mean
the data get converted to NDBC_HISTORIC after that. To query an NDBC_HISTORIC data set, you cannot specify the current year.
So it is possible to not have access to select data for many months depending on the date.

2) Station lists.
For each SOURCE, a pre established station list is provided. The User may change that atwill.
The station lists are expectex to be in the same directory as the yaml files

The defauilt lists are:

NOAA_STATIONS: 
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/noaa_stations.csv"
NDBC_BUOYS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/ndbc_buoys.csv"
NDBC_HISTORIC:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/ndbc_historic_buoys.csv"
USGS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/USGS_coastal_stations.csv"
USGS_RIVERS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/USGS_river_stations.csv"
CONTRAILS_COASTAL:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/contrails_stations_coastal.csv"
CONTRAILS_RIVERS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/contrails_stations_rivers.csv"

Generally, these are simply lists of station ids. However, the NDBC Buoy data are a little different. The NDBC server will return the
lon/lat values for the specified statiobn but NOT the station name. We generally want the station name for presentation and so we 
manually add the station name to the NDBC and NDBC_HISTORIC input files as an extra column. Note also, one could add a station name column
to any of the input station csv files. This is often convenient to the user. The AST software will ignore those names except for NDBC data.

3) Data Products. Several data products are available for stations. The NAMES of the products are those defined by the AST software.
AST manages conversion to source-specific names for the data.. 
A typical set of possible products for a given source are listed below.

All products are returned in metric units.
The VARIABLE name is an artifact and is not needed for observation fetching

NOAA_STATIONS: 
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/noaa_stations.csv"
    VARIABLE: "zeta"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "water_level"
        PRED: "predictions"
        PRES: "air_pressure"
        WSPD: "wind_speed"

CONTRAILS_RIVERS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/contrails_stations_rivers.csv"
    VARIABLE: "zeta"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "river_water_level"
        FVOL: "river_flow_volume"
        WSEL: "river_stream_elevation"
        PRES: "air_pressure"

CONTRAILS_COASTAL:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/harvester_stations/supporting_data/contrails_stations_coastal.csv"
    VARIABLE: "zeta"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "coastal_water_level"
        PRES: "air_pressure"

NDBC_BUOYS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/ndbc_buoys.csv"
    VARIABLE: "swan_HS"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "wave_height"
        PRES: "air_pressure"
        WSPD: "wind_speed"

NDBC_HISTORIC:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/ndbc_historic_buoys.csv"
    VARIABLE: "swan_HS"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "wave_height"
        PRES: "air_pressure"
        WSPD: "wind_speed"

USGS_RIVERS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/USGS_river_stations.csv"
    VARIABLE: "zeta"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "water_level"
        FVOL: "river_flow_volume"
        PRES: "air_pressure"

USGS:
    STATION_FILE: "./AST_gridstations/observations_data/supporting_data/USGS_coastal_stations.csv"
    VARIABLE: "zeta"
    SOURCES:
        WATR: "water_level"
        PRES: "air_pressure"













Generally, a user may supply any set of products to any station and AST will accomodate. However, for product that do not exist at that station, 
the resulting data set will simply be empty. Also to maximize parallelism, we only specify a single product per inpput file.





The "harvester_stations" data are simply the current list of NOAA,NDBC,CONTRAILS station ids that (can) be used by the run_harvester
fetching process. The run_hervester will read the sources_map.yaml file and attempt to process every source/product that is listed. Individual
files with unique nomenclature will be created. These are resulting files are then expected to be ingested by the Harvester DB system
